//Mediastinal vessels - Pulmonary veins

Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
And	I'm on Page 09 of Cardio MRI
And I select 'Finding' radio button
And I select 'Mediastinal vessels' from the dropdown menu

When I select 'Pulmonary veins' radio button
Then 'Rightâ€“sided accessory pulmonary vein (RAPV)' radio button is enabled
And 'Left accessory pulmonary vein (LAPV)' radio button is enabled
And 'Partial Anomalous Pulmonary Venous Connection (PAPVC)' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Partial Anomalous Pulmonary Venous Connection (PAPVC)' radio button
Then 'Outlet of the right upper pulmonary vein into right atrium / VCS' radio button is enabled
And 'Scimitar syndrome' radio button is enabled
